	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>Warrior opinion</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Oct 16th 4:34 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=129573><span id= >Tirram</span></a><br><span id=notbold>2 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I have one of these on my warrior atm,&nbsp;&nbsp;picked it up because basically nobody else wanted it and it was going to rot.   While it is nice dmg/dly and a 41% haste item,  it really in the long run has lowered my DPS on boss mob type mobs (L63-70) due to the fact that my pierce caps at 240.  I do more damage if I equip a 1h slash or 1h blunt with same ratio.   ( note,  also have 41% haste in belt )    So for a warrior who just wants to get into the 41% haste bracket it is nice,  but honestly if you can do glyphed  you prolly are able to do parts if not all of NToV.   there are I think 3 belts and the CoL ( claw of lightning ) from there with 41% haste also.<br><br>As for the rogue argument,  I think it is a nice rogue item,  but there are good arguments either way for using this or the ragebringer.   1% more haste? or the 40atk.   somewhat of a toss-up.  </p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
